<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1914-08-10T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1914-08-10T00:00:00-05:00" n="24" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d24">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 835.001/35a.</note>
                        <head>
                            <hi rend="italic">President <persName type="from">Wilson</persName> to
                                the <gloss type="to">Vice President of Argentina</gloss>.</hi>
                        </head>
                        <opener>
                            <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.]</seg>
                        </opener>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">The White House</hi>, <lb/>
                                    <hi rend="italic">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1914-08-10">
                                    <hi rend="italic">August 10, 1914</hi></date>.</dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>It is with deep regret that I learn of the death of His Excellency
                            President Saenz Pena and I hasten to express to the Government and
                            people of Argentina the sincere sympathy of the Government and people of
                            the United States of America and my own in this great loss sustained by
                            your country.</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">Woodrow Wilson</hi></signed>.</closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>